You should be comparing a character against _character_ literals, not string literals:

    public static boolean isVowel(char c) {
        c = Character.toLowerCase(c);
        return c == &#39;a&#39; || c == &#39;e&#39; || c == &#39;i&#39; || c == &#39;o&#39; || c == &#39;u&#39;;
    }

You could try to streamline the above code by instead using a set to hold all possible acceptable input values:

    public static boolean isVowel(char c) {
        Set&lt;Character&gt; chars = new HashSet&lt;&gt;(Arrays.asList(&#39;a&#39;, &#39;e&#39;, &#39;i&#39;, &#39;o&#39;, &#39;u&#39;));
        return chars.contains(Character.toLowerCase(c));
    }

